    • Field Detail

      • autocolorscale

        @Option
public Boolean autocolorscale
        Has an effect only if "marker.line.color" is set to a numerical array. Determines whether the colorscale is a default palette ("autocolorscale: true") or the palette determined by "marker.line.colorscale". In case "colorscale" is unspecified or "autocolorscale" is true, the default palette will be chosen according to whether numbers in the "color" array are all positive, all negative or mixed.

      • cauto

        @Option
public Boolean cauto
        Has an effect only if "marker.line.color" is set to a numerical array and "cmin", "cmax" are set by the user. In this case, it controls whether the range of colors in "colorscale" is mapped to the range of values in the "color" array ("cauto: true"), or the "cmin"/"cmax" values ("cauto: false").

        Default: false (when "cmin", "cmax" are set by the user)

      • cmax

        @Option
public Integer cmax
        The upper bound of the color domain. Value should be associated to the "marker.line.color" array index, and if set, "marker.line.cmin" must be set as well.

      • cmin

        @Option
public Integer cmin
        The lower bound of the color domain. Value should be associated to the "marker.line.color" array index, and if set, "marker.line.cmax" must be set as well.

      • color$array

        @Option(value="color")
public int[] color$array
        The line color. Array elements are mapped to the colorscale relative to the max and min values of the array or relative to "cmin" and "cmax" if set.

      • color$string

        @Option(value="color")
public String color$string
        Sets all line colors to the same value.

      • colorscale

        @Option
public Object colorscale
        The colorscale and only has an effect if "marker.line.color" is set to a numerical array. The colorscale must be an array containing arrays mapping a normalized value to an rgb, rgba, hex, hsl, hsv, or named color string. At minimum, a mapping for the lowest (0) and highest (1) values are required. For example, "[[0, "rgb(0,0,255)", [1, "rgb(255,0,0)"]]". To control the bounds of the colorscale in color space, use "marker.line.cmin" and "marker.line.cmax". Alternatively, "colorscale" may be a palette name string of the following list: Greys, YlGnBu, Greens, YlOrRd, Bluered, RdBu, Reds, Blues, Picnic, Rainbow, Portland, Jet, Hot, Blackbody, Earth, Electric, Viridis, Cividis

      • outliercolor

        @Option
public String outliercolor
        The border line color of the outlier sample points.

        Default: marker color

      • outlierwidth

        @Option
public Integer outlierwidth
        Sets the border line width (in px) of the outlier sample points.

        Default: 1

      • reversescale

        @Option
public Boolean reversescale
        Has an effect only if "marker.line.color" is set to a numerical array. Reverses the color mapping if true ("cmin" will correspond to the last color in the array and "cmax" will correspond to the first color).

      • width$array

        @Option(value="width")
public int[] width$array
        The width (in px) of the lines bounding the marker points.

      • width$number

        @Option(value="width")
public Integer width$number
        The width (in px) of the lines bounding the marker points to the same value.
